&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited from competent, able practitioners who wish to provide dynamic support to the theatre Trauma and Orthopaedic team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The operating department includes 16 in-patient theatres within the Division plus the Surgical Day Unit (3 GA theatres and Paediatric Day facility.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The theatres provide an operating service to the following clinical specialities: General Surgery, Gynaecology, Urology, Obstetrics, Plastic Surgery, Orthopaedics, Maxilo-facial, Robotic Surgery, Neurosurgery, ENT and IVF.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is also provision for 2 x dedicated emergency theatres and 2 x dedicated Trauma theatres within the complex.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The division is committed to staff development and offers an excellent competency based training package. Good communication and organisational skills and the ability to work as part of a team are essential to this post.&lt;/p&gt;
